1
00:00:05,571 --> 00:00:07,241
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,311 --> 00:00:08,981
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,841 --> 00:00:12,381
What did you just say?

4
00:00:13,111 --> 00:00:15,281
Are you asking me for a divorce?

5
00:00:16,751 --> 00:00:18,751
Yes. Let's get a divorce.

6
00:00:19,221 --> 00:00:21,591
- Dad.
- Seriously, what's gotten into you?

7
00:00:22,321 --> 00:00:25,121
Seong Mi.
He's had a little too much to drink.

8
00:00:25,531 --> 00:00:29,201
- It's just the alcohol talking.
- It's not. I'm serious.

9
00:00:29,761 --> 00:00:33,101
- Jeong Han.
- How can you start this?

10
00:00:33,401 --> 00:00:34,831
As if you've done nothing wrong.

11
00:00:35,301 --> 00:00:38,301
Fine. I haven't done anything right.
That's why I want a divorce.

12
00:00:38,671 --> 00:00:41,871
And even if I put myself
in your shoes,

13
00:00:42,281 --> 00:00:43,841
you're too good for me.

14
00:00:44,111 --> 00:00:47,881
Besides, didn't you say
you regret marrying me?

15
00:00:49,751 --> 00:00:52,291
How could you say that
in front of Mother?

16
00:00:52,821 --> 00:00:54,591
You can't say it in front of my mom,

17
00:00:55,051 --> 00:00:56,621
so I'm saying it for you.

18
00:00:57,591 --> 00:00:58,621
Jeong Han.

19
00:00:58,891 --> 00:01:01,591
I know you're drunk, but still.
How could you say that?

20
00:01:01,831 --> 00:01:02,861
In front of Woo Jae.

21
00:01:04,231 --> 00:01:06,331
Seong Mi, it looks like
something happened to him.

22
00:01:07,231 --> 00:01:09,801
Hey, where on earth
did you drink so much?

23
00:01:12,641 --> 00:01:15,881
At Mr. Go Il Sik's funeral.

24
00:01:16,541 --> 00:01:17,541
What?

25
00:01:18,241 --> 00:01:19,751
Wait, that gentleman...

26
00:01:21,181 --> 00:01:22,321
He passed away?

27
00:01:22,621 --> 00:01:23,621
Yes.

28
00:01:24,321 --> 00:01:26,921
I waited for his family to arrive
and for the wake to be set up,

29
00:01:28,691 --> 00:01:30,461
and I had a few drinks
at the funeral home.

30
00:01:30,891 --> 00:01:31,961
I'm sorry.

31
00:01:32,691 --> 00:01:35,391
Then you should have called
and told us.

32
00:01:35,631 --> 00:01:39,571
Seong Mi, that's what happened.
If you could just...

33
00:01:40,771 --> 00:01:42,141
be a little understanding...

34
00:01:42,841 --> 00:01:45,471
Right. I should be understanding.

35
00:01:46,111 --> 00:01:47,941
So I'm the only one who has to be
understanding. Is that it?

36
00:01:50,441 --> 00:01:52,881
Here you go again,
making me out to be the bad guy.

37
00:01:54,011 --> 00:01:56,351
I'm the villain who's always...

38
00:01:56,351 --> 00:01:58,381
picking on
poor, innocent you, right?

39
00:02:01,121 --> 00:02:02,161
No...

40
00:02:16,001 --> 00:02:17,101
Dad.

41
00:02:28,751 --> 00:02:31,251
Oh, honey.
That's not going to do it.

42
00:02:32,021 --> 00:02:34,951
Just throw everything
until you feel better.

43
00:02:38,221 --> 00:02:39,761
That man who passed away...

44
00:02:40,831 --> 00:02:43,801
Jeong Han saved his life
a few years ago.

45
00:02:44,561 --> 00:02:47,571
He was always so worried about him,

46
00:02:47,571 --> 00:02:49,301
so it's a real shame this happened.

47
00:02:51,301 --> 00:02:52,341
I know.

48
00:02:52,971 --> 00:02:54,611
I know exactly how he feels, but...

49
00:02:55,641 --> 00:02:57,111
I know how you feel, too.

50
00:02:57,911 --> 00:03:01,811
He said that because he's drunk.
Just forget you heard it, okay?

51
00:03:03,321 --> 00:03:04,481
I'm sorry.

52
00:03:05,321 --> 00:03:08,891
Mother, why do you always apologize
for our mistakes?

53
00:03:10,161 --> 00:03:11,291
I do?

54
00:03:11,421 --> 00:03:14,691
Because you do this,
I always end up forgiving him.

55
00:03:15,161 --> 00:03:19,301
And what if you don't?
Are you really going to split up?

56
00:03:20,431 --> 00:03:21,771
How could I?

57
00:03:22,541 --> 00:03:23,871
I have nowhere else to go.

58
00:03:24,371 --> 00:03:26,911
I don't have a family to go back to,
or a mother of my own.

59
00:03:27,341 --> 00:03:30,441
You're my mother.
Where am I supposed to go?

60
00:03:34,481 --> 00:03:35,951
- Dad, come on.
- Let go of me.

61
00:03:35,951 --> 00:03:37,681
- Come on, let's go.
- Hey!

62
00:03:37,781 --> 00:03:39,191
- Hurry up.
- Oh, for crying out loud.

63
00:03:41,451 --> 00:03:43,261
If anyone's leaving,
it should be him.

64
00:03:44,661 --> 00:03:45,761
Exactly.

65
00:03:46,661 --> 00:03:49,631
Hey, you better straighten up,
or you'll be the one kicked out.

66
00:03:54,471 --> 00:03:55,471
What?

67
00:03:57,841 --> 00:04:00,011
I'm sorry.

68
00:04:09,751 --> 00:04:11,981
I'm thinking of growing it out.

69
00:04:12,081 --> 00:04:15,351
- You'd look pretty either way.
- This is my hair without bangs.

70
00:04:18,461 --> 00:04:20,561
I was so sure
there was something between them.

71
00:04:22,961 --> 00:04:27,431
Your brother and Seong Mi made up.
They're all talk.

72
00:04:27,631 --> 00:04:29,471
I don't think
they're actually getting a divorce.

73
00:04:30,541 --> 00:04:31,541
I hope not.

74
00:04:33,741 --> 00:04:36,941
I'm sorry for mentioning the deposit
to Seong Mi.

75
00:04:38,141 --> 00:04:42,051
I only did it because I was mad
that you were being mean to me.

76
00:04:43,321 --> 00:04:44,451
So...

77
00:04:45,381 --> 00:04:47,391
it's your turn to apologize to me.

78
00:04:48,691 --> 00:04:50,961
Apologize. To me.

79
00:04:55,061 --> 00:04:56,101
I'm sorry.

80
00:04:56,961 --> 00:04:59,171
I just lost my temper
because I was angry about my uncle.

81
00:05:01,001 --> 00:05:04,271
I figured. Your uncle is
a real piece of work, isn't he?

82
00:05:07,511 --> 00:05:09,481
Mother's calling.
Hurry up and come out.

83
00:05:15,081 --> 00:05:16,721
Was I mistaken?

84
00:05:18,051 --> 00:05:19,991
I don't think
she's cheating on me after all.

85
00:05:26,491 --> 00:05:29,101
We are going to keep holding
the memorial every year.

86
00:05:30,201 --> 00:05:32,601
I do not want people saying
I am neglecting my duties...

87
00:05:32,601 --> 00:05:33,731
now that my husband is gone.

88
00:05:34,471 --> 00:05:38,171
But I'll take care of it on my own,
simply and quietly.

89
00:05:38,501 --> 00:05:40,171
So, you guys don't need
to worry about it anymore.

90
00:05:43,881 --> 00:05:44,881
And...

91
00:05:45,541 --> 00:05:48,151
a family shouldn't go to bed
angry at each other.

92
00:05:48,711 --> 00:05:50,681
Let's all make up
before we go to sleep, okay?

93
00:05:51,681 --> 00:05:54,491
We already made up
in our room, Mother.

94
00:05:56,961 --> 00:05:58,421
Seong Mi,
please don't be upset anymore.

95
00:05:59,361 --> 00:06:03,401
I don't regret using
our security deposit to help...

96
00:06:03,631 --> 00:06:04,701
with your clinic.

97
00:06:05,261 --> 00:06:06,671
She means it, Seong Mi.

98
00:06:09,601 --> 00:06:10,601
I think...

99
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:13,441
I'm about to land another show.

100
00:06:14,371 --> 00:06:15,371
Really?

101
00:06:16,081 --> 00:06:19,211
As soon as I get the advance,
we will pay the salaries first.

102
00:06:20,481 --> 00:06:21,681
That's great news!

103
00:06:22,011 --> 00:06:24,351
We couldn't even make
our savings deposit this month.

104
00:06:25,181 --> 00:06:27,521
Mom, it feels like
you're taking on too much work.

105
00:06:28,621 --> 00:06:31,691
He's right. You're already so busy.
Aren't you doing too much?

106
00:06:32,391 --> 00:06:35,231
No, it's fine.
You know I was made for TV.

107
00:06:35,431 --> 00:06:36,601
It's actually pretty fun.

108
00:06:37,031 --> 00:06:39,301
Good.
You're staying the night, right?

109
00:06:39,801 --> 00:06:40,801
Sorry?

110
00:06:41,471 --> 00:06:45,241
- Well...
- Yes. Mom, you should stay over.

111
00:06:45,671 --> 00:06:48,471
That's right. Especially now,
you two should be sharing a room.

112
00:06:49,141 --> 00:06:50,511
Sharing a room?

113
00:06:52,651 --> 00:06:53,781
You're going to sleep in my room?

114
00:06:54,481 --> 00:06:56,451
I'm sleeping in Ju Ah's room.

115
00:06:57,281 --> 00:07:01,251
Woo Jae. Have you heard from Ju Ah?

116
00:07:01,621 --> 00:07:04,861
- No. Her phone's still off.
- Dear...

117
00:07:05,761 --> 00:07:07,991
She must be really upset.

118
00:07:08,591 --> 00:07:11,101
For sure.
After being humiliated like that.

119
00:07:11,461 --> 00:07:14,771
- Still, she's not coming home?
- What's wrong now?

120
00:07:15,071 --> 00:07:16,871
Is something wrong with Ju Ah?

121
00:07:21,771 --> 00:07:23,381
Why? What?

122
00:07:25,911 --> 00:07:27,711
My existence...

123
00:07:28,881 --> 00:07:33,791
wasn't the fruit of their love,
but just a mistake!

124
00:07:36,561 --> 00:07:37,691
It was like...

125
00:07:38,621 --> 00:07:42,831
I've spent my whole life
feeling abandoned, I guess?

126
00:07:46,931 --> 00:07:49,501
That's why
I tried to work so much harder.

127
00:07:49,941 --> 00:07:54,511
More than anyone,
I just wanted my parents' approval.

128
00:07:56,341 --> 00:07:57,441
But today,

129
00:07:58,241 --> 00:08:02,951
I just crashed
and burned spectacularly.

130
00:08:03,751 --> 00:08:05,781
I can't even go home.

131
00:08:11,021 --> 00:08:15,231
I wish I'd never been born...

132
00:08:24,541 --> 00:08:28,441
I should've just never been born.

133
00:08:34,511 --> 00:08:35,511
What?

134
00:08:36,781 --> 00:08:38,021
My teddy bear.

135
00:08:38,551 --> 00:08:40,951
Teddy, where are you going?

136
00:08:41,351 --> 00:08:46,131
- Hey, I didn't abandon you. Oh, no.
- What?

137
00:08:50,001 --> 00:08:51,031
Don't tell me...

138
00:08:51,761 --> 00:08:53,531
The person it happened to...

139
00:08:54,131 --> 00:08:58,141
could be so humiliated
they want to die, you know?

140
00:09:01,141 --> 00:09:02,811
(Danger: Sudden Deep Water
Fatal Accidents Have Occurred)

141
00:09:02,881 --> 00:09:04,041
(Fatal Accidents Have Occurred)

142
00:09:05,711 --> 00:09:06,881
Darn it, seriously...

143
00:09:07,281 --> 00:09:08,411
Hey, you!

144
00:09:14,621 --> 00:09:15,791
Are you trying to kill yourself?

145
00:09:17,861 --> 00:09:18,921
Me?

146
00:09:20,561 --> 00:09:24,331
- You're not, right?
- Of course not. Why would I?

147
00:09:25,001 --> 00:09:27,471
I'm still alive and kicking!

148
00:09:29,671 --> 00:09:30,701
Right.

149
00:09:32,001 --> 00:09:33,941
You're not dead,
but you sure are drunk.

150
00:09:34,541 --> 00:09:36,041
But you...

151
00:09:36,411 --> 00:09:38,541
Have you been following me
this whole time?

152
00:09:39,251 --> 00:09:42,211
Darn it,
are you some kind of pervert?

153
00:09:42,351 --> 00:09:43,451
A pervert?

154
00:09:44,681 --> 00:09:46,651
- No, I'm not.
- Whatever.

155
00:09:47,021 --> 00:09:48,421
Don't come any closer.

156
00:09:49,821 --> 00:09:52,461
Fine. Get out of the water.
I'll help you.

157
00:09:52,591 --> 00:09:56,931
Hey! What, so you can grab me?
Stay away.

158
00:09:57,001 --> 00:10:01,631
- This is a warning.
- Gosh, okay. I won't grab you.

159
00:10:02,841 --> 00:10:04,071
- Oh, no!
- Good grief.

160
00:10:09,211 --> 00:10:10,541
Gosh, that scared me.

161
00:10:15,451 --> 00:10:16,951
Hey, my hand...

162
00:10:22,691 --> 00:10:25,821
I'm going to die! Help... Help me!

163
00:10:26,131 --> 00:10:28,331
Help me! Please, help me!
I'm going to die...

164
00:10:42,471 --> 00:10:44,111
You really won't help me?

165
00:10:44,241 --> 00:10:47,411
You said you'd call the cops on me
as a pervert if I grabbed you.

166
00:10:47,751 --> 00:10:52,121
Well... Who goes around
following someone...

167
00:10:52,181 --> 00:10:53,621
in the middle of the night
like this?

168
00:10:54,421 --> 00:10:55,421
Unbelievable.

169
00:11:22,651 --> 00:11:23,781
Why are you following me?

170
00:11:24,121 --> 00:11:26,021
Are you some kind of pervert?

171
00:11:28,691 --> 00:11:31,891
Well, I'm so sorry to ask,

172
00:11:32,361 --> 00:11:34,491
but my phone got wet,

173
00:11:34,491 --> 00:11:36,601
so I can't call or look anything up.

174
00:11:37,801 --> 00:11:41,131
And of course,
my mobile pay isn't working either.

175
00:11:44,671 --> 00:11:47,741
If you could let me make one call,
I swear I'll make it up to you.

176
00:11:52,981 --> 00:11:53,981
Here.

177
00:11:54,651 --> 00:11:56,951
Thank you so much. Really.

178
00:12:01,291 --> 00:12:02,991
What? What was it?

179
00:12:03,421 --> 00:12:06,831
Woo Jae's number...
Zero, one, zero, three, two, three?

180
00:12:07,231 --> 00:12:08,531
Three, two, two, zero?

181
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:10,061
No, that's not it.

182
00:12:10,701 --> 00:12:12,461
Darn it. This is driving me crazy.
What was it?

183
00:12:12,931 --> 00:12:14,331
You can't remember the number?

184
00:12:15,371 --> 00:12:16,541
Not even your home number?

185
00:12:16,671 --> 00:12:18,771
Well...

186
00:12:28,781 --> 00:12:29,821
Welcome.

187
00:12:30,521 --> 00:12:32,221
Sorry, I'm late.

188
00:12:32,421 --> 00:12:35,651
You sure are. I had everything ready
and thought you weren't coming.

189
00:12:35,821 --> 00:12:36,921
How could I not?

190
00:12:37,221 --> 00:12:39,391
The Seonpo-ri Gaetdari
Samhap Meal...

191
00:12:39,591 --> 00:12:41,561
from Episode 81
of "Everyday Meals Across Korea."

192
00:12:41,761 --> 00:12:44,201
I've been waiting for this
since I booked it two months ago.

193
00:12:45,631 --> 00:12:47,701
But there are two of you.

194
00:12:48,001 --> 00:12:50,301
But you only booked
the guesthouse package for one.

195
00:12:50,301 --> 00:12:53,611
Oh, well... It's a long story.

196
00:12:53,841 --> 00:12:58,441
- Do you have any spare rooms?
- No, we're all booked for tonight.

197
00:12:58,541 --> 00:12:59,581
I see.

198
00:12:59,881 --> 00:13:03,521
I booked the rooftop too,
so I guess I can sleep there.

199
00:13:07,191 --> 00:13:08,521
Go on in, wash up,
and get some sleep.

200
00:13:11,461 --> 00:13:13,461
- Thank you.
- Sure.

201
00:13:24,671 --> 00:13:27,011
Here, change into these.

202
00:13:28,511 --> 00:13:29,581
And...

203
00:13:30,581 --> 00:13:31,741
Make sure you lock the door.

204
00:13:32,811 --> 00:13:35,051
You never know.
There might be a pervert lurking.

205
00:13:39,221 --> 00:13:40,221
The nerve of him...

206
00:13:51,501 --> 00:13:54,501
Come on. Please turn on.

207
00:13:59,911 --> 00:14:01,971
It won't turn on.

208
00:14:08,111 --> 00:14:09,311
I smell meat.

209
00:14:19,691 --> 00:14:20,691
Hey.

210
00:14:21,291 --> 00:14:23,701
- Feeling a little more sober?
- Yes.

211
00:14:26,831 --> 00:14:31,341
Apparently, you can see the mudflats
and the moonlight here at once.

212
00:14:31,401 --> 00:14:32,701
That's why they call it
the Gaetdari Garden.

213
00:14:33,511 --> 00:14:34,711
I see.

214
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:37,381
- Have a seat.
- Okay.

215
00:14:44,151 --> 00:14:47,951
You hardly touched your duck.
Have some. It's Gaetdari Samhap.

216
00:14:49,791 --> 00:14:51,891
- Okay.
- Here. This is...

217
00:14:51,961 --> 00:14:53,891
- I really shouldn't...
- Hair of the dog.

218
00:14:54,691 --> 00:14:59,301
The owner brews it himself
with rice grown in the sea breeze.

219
00:14:59,461 --> 00:15:01,301
I see.

220
00:15:02,031 --> 00:15:04,801
All right.
You take this aged kimchi,

221
00:15:05,101 --> 00:15:08,341
put some perfectly cooked brisket
on top,

222
00:15:08,871 --> 00:15:13,781
top it with scallop and abalone,
roll it all up,

223
00:15:13,951 --> 00:15:18,281
and dip it in this sauce
made from plum syrup! Like this.

224
00:15:19,791 --> 00:15:20,951
All right then.

225
00:15:30,261 --> 00:15:32,361
- Incredible.
- It's amazing, right?

226
00:15:32,661 --> 00:15:37,201
The brisket's savory fat mellows out
the acidity of the aged kimchi.

227
00:15:37,271 --> 00:15:40,841
Then just as the sweetness
of the scallop washes over you,

228
00:15:40,911 --> 00:15:45,541
the sauce comes in with a kick.
Then, a sip of this makgeolli.

229
00:15:45,881 --> 00:15:46,881
Oh, yes.

230
00:15:51,751 --> 00:15:54,021
The perfect finishing touch.

231
00:15:54,851 --> 00:15:58,361
You really know your food.
Hold on. I'll make you another one.

232
00:16:04,701 --> 00:16:09,031
You seem to be on vacation.
I'm so sorry for ruining it for you.

233
00:16:09,901 --> 00:16:13,841
I made a huge mistake today
and lost my job.

234
00:16:13,911 --> 00:16:16,311
But I just couldn't bring myself
to go home,

235
00:16:17,081 --> 00:16:19,951
so I just hopped on the first bus
that came along,

236
00:16:20,011 --> 00:16:22,551
and I guess I zoned out
and ended up here at the last stop.

237
00:16:23,981 --> 00:16:28,591
I'm really not like this at all.
I don't know what's gotten into me.

238
00:16:28,891 --> 00:16:32,291
I've been a mess, making mistakes
and causing so much trouble...

239
00:16:33,061 --> 00:16:34,331
I'm so sorry.

240
00:16:34,461 --> 00:16:38,561
It happens. We all have those days
when it feels like you're in a fog.

241
00:16:40,031 --> 00:16:43,441
In Spain,
if someone makes many mistakes,

242
00:16:44,041 --> 00:16:46,771
people say,
"Oh, they must be in love."

243
00:16:47,611 --> 00:16:51,311
But Koreans are a little tough
on mistakes, aren't they?

244
00:16:52,411 --> 00:16:54,311
Thank you
for being so understanding.

245
00:16:57,621 --> 00:16:58,621
What?

246
00:16:58,621 --> 00:17:02,451
I said I had fun today.
I'm okay, so please cheer up.

247
00:17:03,991 --> 00:17:05,061
Thank you.

248
00:17:15,131 --> 00:17:18,501
Weren't you sleeping
in Ju Ah's room?

249
00:17:18,501 --> 00:17:19,771
The door's locked.

250
00:17:20,511 --> 00:17:22,511
What?
So, you're going to sleep here?

251
00:17:22,871 --> 00:17:24,341
What, you want me
to sleep out in the hall?

252
00:17:25,481 --> 00:17:27,081
No, I'll go sleep
somewhere else then.

253
00:17:27,411 --> 00:17:29,181
Just sleep here.

254
00:17:29,481 --> 00:17:32,281
If not, your mother will worry
that we've been fighting again.

255
00:17:33,051 --> 00:17:34,651
Good grief.

256
00:17:37,321 --> 00:17:39,591
What are you waiting for?
Go and wash up.

257
00:17:39,891 --> 00:17:40,891
What?

258
00:17:41,631 --> 00:17:42,861
You want me to wash up?

259
00:17:43,331 --> 00:17:44,761
Were you not going to?

260
00:17:44,931 --> 00:17:45,961
No.

261
00:17:46,361 --> 00:17:49,371
No, I mean... Of course, I will.
I'll go wash up.

262
00:17:55,311 --> 00:17:57,911
But why would she tell me
to wash up?

263
00:17:58,741 --> 00:18:00,611
It's kind of scaring me.

264
00:18:12,421 --> 00:18:13,491
What's this about?

265
00:18:20,531 --> 00:18:24,271
- You think you're sleeping here?
- Where else am I supposed to sleep?

266
00:18:24,601 --> 00:18:27,041
Sleep on the floor.
I already put out your bedding.

267
00:18:27,211 --> 00:18:30,241
I can't sleep on the floor.
My back will kill me.

268
00:18:30,311 --> 00:18:32,041
So you expect me
to sleep on the floor?

269
00:18:32,211 --> 00:18:35,081
What's the big deal?
Why is it okay for me, but not you?

270
00:18:35,551 --> 00:18:36,881
You're being so childish.

271
00:18:39,221 --> 00:18:41,291
- Fine, rock-paper-scissors for it.
- Forget it.

272
00:18:41,591 --> 00:18:43,191
Talk about childish.

273
00:18:43,461 --> 00:18:46,091
Seriously, if this was the plan,
why did you even tell me to wash up?

274
00:18:47,061 --> 00:18:50,631
You should wash up before bed.
You won't do it unless I say so.

275
00:18:50,831 --> 00:18:52,761
A doctor, of all people,
being so unhygienic.

276
00:18:52,861 --> 00:18:54,431
I wash up before work, okay?

277
00:18:54,431 --> 00:18:56,871
And it's not like
I treat patients with my body.

278
00:18:57,871 --> 00:19:01,711
But what's with you asking
why I told you to wash up?

279
00:19:02,611 --> 00:19:04,241
What exactly were you expecting?

280
00:19:05,041 --> 00:19:08,151
What do you mean, expecting?
I wasn't expecting anything.

281
00:19:08,411 --> 00:19:11,821
My gosh. You think I want to sleep
in the same room as you?

282
00:19:11,881 --> 00:19:14,921
You snore like a freight train,
you know. Unbelievable.

283
00:19:14,991 --> 00:19:16,191
You're going to sleep
in those clothes?

284
00:19:16,821 --> 00:19:18,361
Gosh, whatever.
It's too much trouble.

285
00:19:20,131 --> 00:19:24,301
If you ever mention divorce again
in front of your mother,

286
00:19:24,361 --> 00:19:25,431
you'll regret it.

287
00:19:26,061 --> 00:19:27,631
Fine, I get it.

288
00:19:31,301 --> 00:19:34,211
The more I think about it,
the more ridiculous it is.

289
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:39,511
What? You'll grant me a divorce
because I look miserable?

290
00:19:41,011 --> 00:19:42,481
Let's just get some sleep.

291
00:19:42,811 --> 00:19:45,521
You pretend to be the nice guy
who's putting up with everything,

292
00:19:45,651 --> 00:19:49,051
but you just make me uncomfortable.
That's being passive-aggressive.

293
00:19:49,351 --> 00:19:52,161
Passive-aggressive behavior,
to use the technical term.

294
00:19:54,991 --> 00:19:57,461
Gosh, I can't even stand
the sight of him.

295
00:20:01,271 --> 00:20:02,901
- Cheers!
- Hey.

296
00:20:08,611 --> 00:20:10,441
Oh, this is nice.

297
00:20:11,811 --> 00:20:12,911
Oh, boy.

298
00:20:13,411 --> 00:20:14,651
Man...

299
00:20:16,481 --> 00:20:17,551
By the way,

300
00:20:18,421 --> 00:20:19,991
about that wardrobe malfunction
on the shopping network.

301
00:20:21,391 --> 00:20:22,651
You said
it was a simple mistake, right?

302
00:20:24,091 --> 00:20:26,021
Then why can't you go back to work?

303
00:20:26,461 --> 00:20:29,291
Because you're too embarrassed
about it?

304
00:20:30,661 --> 00:20:35,101
Because I feel like I don't deserve
to design clothes anymore.

305
00:20:36,641 --> 00:20:37,671
I...

306
00:20:38,271 --> 00:20:42,541
was actually relieved
that it happened to me.

307
00:20:43,511 --> 00:20:47,381
One of my customers could have gone
through that, you know?

308
00:20:48,051 --> 00:20:52,581
I could have ruined
someone's wonderful day.

309
00:20:54,621 --> 00:20:55,821
You know,

310
00:20:56,291 --> 00:20:58,361
I love seeing people happy
in the clothes I make.

311
00:20:58,591 --> 00:21:02,291
I love making people happy.

312
00:21:04,761 --> 00:21:05,901
That's admirable.

313
00:21:06,871 --> 00:21:09,771
Someone who creates happiness.

314
00:21:13,771 --> 00:21:17,041
"Someone who creates happiness."

315
00:21:21,111 --> 00:21:22,611
But why can't you go home?

316
00:21:23,111 --> 00:21:26,021
Isn't family who you're supposed
to lean on during tough times?

317
00:21:28,391 --> 00:21:33,121
My whole family will be there today
for my great-grandfather's memorial.

318
00:21:33,491 --> 00:21:36,361
And it's obvious what happened to me
will be the main topic of gossip.

319
00:21:40,901 --> 00:21:42,901
That sounds nice, actually.
Like a real, lively family.

320
00:21:46,341 --> 00:21:47,811
What's your family like?

321
00:21:52,381 --> 00:21:53,651
I don't know.

322
00:22:00,351 --> 00:22:04,021
My parents divorced
when I was a kid.

323
00:22:05,191 --> 00:22:09,891
My dad remarried right away,
and my young stepmom moved in.

324
00:22:11,761 --> 00:22:16,131
I was worried that as a teenager,
I'd get in the way of the newlyweds,

325
00:22:17,041 --> 00:22:19,141
so I left home and have been
drifting around ever since.

326
00:22:20,041 --> 00:22:23,641
Oh, gosh.
You had to grow up way too fast.

327
00:22:30,921 --> 00:22:34,091
<i>I have been so lonely</i>
<i>and had such a hard time</i>

328
00:22:34,351 --> 00:22:38,521
<i>But it's only a rehearsal</i>

329
00:22:40,231 --> 00:22:43,931
<i>I'm not going to fall down</i>

330
00:22:44,101 --> 00:22:46,901
<i>I got this</i>

331
00:22:53,871 --> 00:22:57,181
That song... It's my favorite.

332
00:22:57,711 --> 00:23:00,111
Really? Mine, too.

333
00:23:04,121 --> 00:23:07,491
Hey, what's your name?

334
00:23:08,591 --> 00:23:09,921
It's a secret.

335
00:23:22,701 --> 00:23:25,901
<i>I have been so lonely</i>
<i>and had such a hard time</i>

336
00:23:26,401 --> 00:23:30,311
<i>But it's only a rehearsal</i>

337
00:23:31,881 --> 00:23:35,411
<i>I'm not going to fall down</i>

338
00:23:35,951 --> 00:23:39,081
<i>I got this</i>

339
00:23:39,181 --> 00:23:41,151
(Gong Ju Ah)

340
00:23:47,961 --> 00:23:49,431
Goodbye, Yang Hyun Bin.

341
00:23:49,891 --> 00:23:51,931
You have to find happiness,
and then come back.

342
00:23:52,631 --> 00:23:53,631
Okay?

343
00:24:12,681 --> 00:24:16,091
Thanks to you,
I tried my best to be happy.

344
00:24:17,391 --> 00:24:18,921
No wonder you looked so familiar.

345
00:24:21,461 --> 00:24:22,631
I'm back,

346
00:24:24,201 --> 00:24:25,201
Gong Ju Ah.

347
00:24:58,631 --> 00:25:00,301
Seong Mi, I wrote this for you.

348
00:25:01,101 --> 00:25:02,231
It's an original song.

349
00:25:09,041 --> 00:25:13,211
<i>The clear tear welling in your eye</i>

350
00:25:15,581 --> 00:25:19,281
<i>Makes my heart rate spike</i>

351
00:25:21,551 --> 00:25:23,561
<i>Ba-dump, ba-dump</i>

352
00:25:24,621 --> 00:25:28,831
<i>You're my own IV fluid,</i>
<i>my private intravenous shot</i>

353
00:25:29,731 --> 00:25:34,201
<i>You are my cure for arrhythmia</i>

354
00:25:34,701 --> 00:25:39,171
<i>You are my personal IV,</i>
<i>my own Band-Aid</i>

355
00:25:39,801 --> 00:25:44,141
<i>You've completely healed</i>
<i>all my wounds</i>

356
00:25:46,441 --> 00:25:48,911
<i>Give me a lifetime prescription</i>

357
00:25:48,981 --> 00:25:52,421
<i>With unlimited refills</i>

358
00:25:56,051 --> 00:25:57,961
Good grief...

359
00:26:04,901 --> 00:26:09,331
I must have been out of my mind.
My frontal lobe must've been frozen.

360
00:26:13,341 --> 00:26:14,341
Darn...

361
00:26:18,711 --> 00:26:19,811
What the...

362
00:26:21,751 --> 00:26:22,811
What was that?

363
00:27:19,171 --> 00:27:20,511
Please...

364
00:27:49,031 --> 00:27:50,131
You scared me!

365
00:27:50,971 --> 00:27:55,341
- Mom? I thought you went home.
- Isn't this my house, too?

366
00:27:55,511 --> 00:27:59,241
Don't tell me you slept with Dad.
In the same bed?

367
00:27:59,641 --> 00:28:02,581
- Unbelievable.
- Don't change the subject.

368
00:28:03,381 --> 00:28:04,951
Where have you been all this time?

369
00:28:06,021 --> 00:28:07,921
Well, I...

370
00:28:08,191 --> 00:28:09,691
Gosh, you reek of alcohol.

371
00:28:14,531 --> 00:28:15,531
You.

372
00:28:16,261 --> 00:28:17,761
What are you wearing?

373
00:28:18,031 --> 00:28:22,401
- Wait. Isn't this a man's shirt?
- No, it's not.

374
00:28:22,531 --> 00:28:23,741
No?

375
00:28:24,341 --> 00:28:25,441
Tell me the truth, right now!

376
00:28:25,501 --> 00:28:28,271
That hurt! What's your problem?
Are you some kind of thug?

377
00:28:28,841 --> 00:28:31,511
And you call yourself
a "love evangelist?"

378
00:28:31,581 --> 00:28:34,381
You're quitting your job. Right now.

379
00:28:34,751 --> 00:28:37,221
Leave your job and start training
to become a specialist doctor.

380
00:28:38,081 --> 00:28:39,351
There you go again.

381
00:28:39,421 --> 00:28:43,521
You've fooled around long enough.
You can't even do your job properly.

382
00:28:43,591 --> 00:28:45,921
Just quit before
you humiliate yourself again.

383
00:28:45,991 --> 00:28:50,831
I bet you were praying I'd fail!
Just waiting for me to mess up.

384
00:28:50,961 --> 00:28:54,871
When your daughter's struggling,
shouldn't you be there for her?

385
00:28:54,871 --> 00:28:58,101
You're the one who messed up.
Why are you taking it out on me?

386
00:28:58,771 --> 00:29:03,411
Projecting your anxiety and guilt.
Psychoanalytically speaking...

387
00:29:03,411 --> 00:29:07,211
Just stop it!
Why are you always analyzing me?

388
00:29:07,281 --> 00:29:09,711
What, am I your patient?
Unbelievable!

389
00:29:10,851 --> 00:29:13,991
Why do you always lock your door?
To keep me out?

390
00:29:14,351 --> 00:29:15,891
To keep you out!

391
00:29:18,421 --> 00:29:19,421
The nerve.

392
00:29:43,851 --> 00:29:44,851
Hello.

393
00:29:45,151 --> 00:29:46,151
Hello.

394
00:29:46,421 --> 00:29:48,691
Right.
The young lady left a while ago.

395
00:29:49,191 --> 00:29:50,621
She did?

396
00:29:53,061 --> 00:29:56,591
That's a shame.
There's clam soup for breakfast.

397
00:29:58,261 --> 00:30:00,501
She should've had some.
Her stomach's probably killing her.

398
00:30:04,401 --> 00:30:06,741
Oh, this is good.

399
00:30:07,941 --> 00:30:09,241
Hey, Ju Ah.

400
00:30:09,671 --> 00:30:12,411
So what's going to happen with work?
Can you not go in starting tomorrow?

401
00:30:12,511 --> 00:30:16,451
How could she? That video of her
is all over the Internet.

402
00:30:16,751 --> 00:30:20,621
People make mistakes.
Why should this stop my work?

403
00:30:20,691 --> 00:30:22,921
That's right. You tell them, Ju Ah.

404
00:30:25,361 --> 00:30:26,361
Seong Mi.

405
00:30:26,991 --> 00:30:30,191
How about you end your lease
and move back in?

406
00:30:30,701 --> 00:30:31,701
What?

407
00:30:32,661 --> 00:30:34,501
Dad, you made it so obvious
that you hate the idea.

408
00:30:35,801 --> 00:30:37,201
Did I?

409
00:30:37,701 --> 00:30:39,701
I'm all for it. A hundred percent.

410
00:30:40,241 --> 00:30:42,511
I'm against it.
Absolutely against it.

411
00:30:45,041 --> 00:30:47,141
Mother, why the sudden suggestion?

412
00:30:48,111 --> 00:30:50,481
You know what they say,
"Out of sight, out of mind."

413
00:30:51,221 --> 00:30:52,981
I think
all this divorce talk started...

414
00:30:52,981 --> 00:30:55,791
- What? Divorce?
- because you two live apart.

415
00:30:56,121 --> 00:31:00,421
Even if you bicker,
isn't it better under one roof?

416
00:31:00,761 --> 00:31:05,031
But Mother, I only moved
because the commute was killing me.

417
00:31:05,761 --> 00:31:09,531
Besides, my lease isn't up yet,
so it'd be hard to break it.

418
00:31:10,371 --> 00:31:14,241
- I can live in your place, Mom.
- Be quiet.

419
00:31:14,641 --> 00:31:15,941
We'll think about it.

420
00:31:16,971 --> 00:31:19,081
What's there for you to think about?

421
00:31:20,681 --> 00:31:23,351
Right, Mom.
Your show is on today, isn't it?

422
00:31:23,411 --> 00:31:24,851
That's right. Let's watch it.

423
00:31:25,181 --> 00:31:26,951
It's probably started already.
Hand me the remote. The remote.

424
00:31:27,021 --> 00:31:30,991
Gosh, do we have to watch that?
Her own family is a train wreck,

425
00:31:31,061 --> 00:31:34,561
- and she tells others how to live.
- Gong Ju Ah.

426
00:31:34,961 --> 00:31:35,961
That's enough.

427
00:31:36,231 --> 00:31:37,231
Yes, ma'am.

428
00:31:39,831 --> 00:31:40,831
What?

429
00:31:43,631 --> 00:31:48,071
First, we respect each other,
and we don't bottle up our emotions.

430
00:31:48,311 --> 00:31:52,911
We've learned to communicate
without blaming each other.

431
00:31:53,811 --> 00:31:56,681
My, I bet every family in Korea
is envious of you.

432
00:31:56,681 --> 00:31:59,421
You're such a perfect,
exemplary family.

433
00:32:00,421 --> 00:32:02,891
What a joke.
Gosh, I can't stand her.

434
00:32:05,291 --> 00:32:08,691
- Maybe I should expose them all.
- Expose what?

435
00:32:09,091 --> 00:32:13,101
I'll say Dr. Han's father-in-law
left his own family for our mom...

436
00:32:13,161 --> 00:32:15,771
and humiliate her so badly
she can't show her face on TV again.

437
00:32:16,171 --> 00:32:19,401
Who would be embarrassed?
Think about it.

438
00:32:19,901 --> 00:32:21,041
Oh, brother.

439
00:32:22,641 --> 00:32:23,641
Hey, Eun Bin.

440
00:32:24,611 --> 00:32:26,811
- Did you know? Your dad...
- What about him?

441
00:32:27,081 --> 00:32:31,581
The woman my husband had a crush on
married Dr. Gong, so he...

442
00:32:31,721 --> 00:32:33,551
married Eun Bin's mom
on the rebound?

443
00:32:36,821 --> 00:32:40,761
The whole family knows.
If you bring it up again,

444
00:32:40,831 --> 00:32:41,831
it'll be the thousandth time.

445
00:32:42,631 --> 00:32:43,691
Have I talked about it that much?

446
00:32:44,631 --> 00:32:48,371
Anyway,
Han Seong Mi is still pretty.

447
00:32:48,431 --> 00:32:50,601
- Right, Dong Ik?
- Pretty? What's pretty about her?

448
00:32:51,001 --> 00:32:52,641
She looks so old,
I can barely recognize her.

449
00:32:54,471 --> 00:32:58,811
Are you blind?
She looks incredible for her age.

450
00:32:59,011 --> 00:33:01,211
I get it. It's just sour grapes
because she's out of your league.

451
00:33:02,781 --> 00:33:04,821
Are you out of your mind?

452
00:33:06,721 --> 00:33:11,621
I think Dr. Han Seong Mi is amazing.
She's so classy and elegant.

453
00:33:11,691 --> 00:33:15,591
That must be why my dad liked her.
Right, Stepmom?

454
00:33:16,631 --> 00:33:20,161
- I suppose so.
- Can you all knock it off?

455
00:33:21,001 --> 00:33:24,341
What a way to start the morning.
Why are we even talking about them?

456
00:33:25,441 --> 00:33:29,911
I hope my future mother-in-law
is just like her. Wait.

457
00:33:29,971 --> 00:33:34,151
They have the perfect guy for me!
Woo Jae!

458
00:33:34,211 --> 00:33:36,511
Hey! Don't you even joke about that.

459
00:33:36,581 --> 00:33:38,381
Do you want to give Grandfather
a heart attack?

460
00:33:38,651 --> 00:33:41,421
And that's not all.
Woo Jae's mom was Dad's first love.

461
00:33:41,651 --> 00:33:44,021
So? That's ancient history.

462
00:33:44,091 --> 00:33:47,291
Eun Bin, listen. You can have
your pick of any man in the world,

463
00:33:47,391 --> 00:33:49,491
and I'll make sure you get
whatever your heart desires, but...

464
00:33:50,261 --> 00:33:52,601
- not him.
- What? Why not?

465
00:33:52,701 --> 00:33:53,961
Because...

466
00:33:55,301 --> 00:33:57,131
the thought of becoming in-laws
with that woman...

467
00:33:57,401 --> 00:33:59,641
I don't have
a single shred of interest in that.

468
00:34:45,421 --> 00:34:46,981
I'm thinking of growing it out.

469
00:34:46,981 --> 00:34:49,921
- You'd look pretty either way.
- This is my hair without bangs.

470
00:34:52,191 --> 00:34:53,191
Right.

471
00:34:53,821 --> 00:34:55,361
It was dark.
My eyes were playing tricks on me.

472
00:34:55,961 --> 00:34:57,361
And the angle was all wrong.

473
00:34:58,631 --> 00:35:02,071
- My darling would never do that.
- Right.

474
00:35:02,501 --> 00:35:05,501
You scared me. Hey, I told you
to act like you don't know me.

475
00:35:05,641 --> 00:35:08,371
Then don't stand
in the middle of the street. Move.

476
00:35:10,741 --> 00:35:13,441
Ji Hu, you should greet your elders
when you see them.

477
00:35:13,511 --> 00:35:15,111
But you just said
to act like we don't know you.

478
00:35:17,081 --> 00:35:18,121
Hello, sir.

479
00:35:19,181 --> 00:35:20,451
You're a handsome kid.

480
00:35:20,851 --> 00:35:22,821
- Isn't he?
- He must take after his dad.

481
00:35:24,791 --> 00:35:28,491
- Does he get good grades?
- Of course. He's incredibly smart.

482
00:35:28,561 --> 00:35:30,061
Oh, that's strange.

483
00:35:30,591 --> 00:35:32,301
I didn't think
you carried the smart gene.

484
00:35:34,371 --> 00:35:36,831
Then why is it
you don't have any kids yet?

485
00:35:37,201 --> 00:35:40,101
Right.
Is it too difficult at her age?

486
00:35:40,601 --> 00:35:43,911
It was better when you were married
and gone. Why did you move back?

487
00:35:44,181 --> 00:35:46,241
Right, your husband
blew all your money,

488
00:35:46,241 --> 00:35:47,651
so you're living with your family.

489
00:35:47,751 --> 00:35:49,751
I'm off. Wait.

490
00:35:49,811 --> 00:35:51,651
Dong Suk, I'm only asking
because I'm genuinely curious.

491
00:35:52,351 --> 00:35:53,981
How much did he lose, exactly?
See you.

492
00:35:55,251 --> 00:35:57,491
- Gosh, can you believe that guy?
- Don't get mad.

493
00:35:58,291 --> 00:35:59,291
He's not wrong, though.

494
00:36:06,301 --> 00:36:08,171
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

495
00:36:11,301 --> 00:36:13,271
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

496
00:36:15,241 --> 00:36:16,241
My gosh.

497
00:36:18,511 --> 00:36:19,911
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

498
00:36:30,151 --> 00:36:31,161
Hello.

499
00:36:32,421 --> 00:36:34,291
Yes. Hello.

500
00:36:35,461 --> 00:36:37,701
Here. This is for you.

501
00:36:42,701 --> 00:36:44,541
Should I do it here?

502
00:36:45,541 --> 00:36:48,411
- Do what?
- Didn't you want my autograph?

503
00:36:49,871 --> 00:36:50,941
No, that's not it.

504
00:36:51,211 --> 00:36:53,911
It's an invitation
to our clinic's grand opening.

505
00:36:54,281 --> 00:36:55,281
I'm sorry?

506
00:36:57,151 --> 00:37:01,251
- Oh, I see.
- Gosh, don't you know who I am?

507
00:37:01,721 --> 00:37:04,151
I'm the wife of the director
of this clinic.

508
00:37:04,491 --> 00:37:05,721
Oh, no. Dr. Han.

509
00:37:05,991 --> 00:37:08,131
You have trouble recognizing faces,
don't you?

510
00:37:08,561 --> 00:37:11,201
Oh, right.
Now, I remember who you are.

511
00:37:12,101 --> 00:37:14,161
You're Yang Dong Ik's second wife.

512
00:37:14,771 --> 00:37:17,771
Aren't you? My apologies.

513
00:37:18,241 --> 00:37:20,641
Your face has changed a bit.
I didn't recognize you.

514
00:37:21,271 --> 00:37:23,071
You must've had some work done,
right?

515
00:37:24,341 --> 00:37:25,441
No, I haven't.

516
00:37:26,081 --> 00:37:29,111
I think your eyes are getting old,
Doctor.

517
00:37:29,551 --> 00:37:31,081
Then again,
you are at that age, aren't you?

518
00:37:36,151 --> 00:37:38,221
Hey, Yang Dong Ik! Long time no see.

519
00:37:44,401 --> 00:37:45,831
I know you two were classmates,

520
00:37:46,301 --> 00:37:48,631
but he has a certain social standing
and reputation now.

521
00:37:48,901 --> 00:37:51,201
Calling him just by his full name...

522
00:37:51,541 --> 00:37:53,741
is hardly appropriate,
don't you think?

523
00:37:54,711 --> 00:37:55,711
Really?

524
00:37:56,141 --> 00:37:59,311
Back in college,
we used to call him Bucket.

525
00:38:01,111 --> 00:38:02,111
Bucket.

526
00:38:02,811 --> 00:38:03,911
Bucket!

527
00:38:04,481 --> 00:38:07,891
My, Doctor, you're so mischievous.

528
00:38:12,721 --> 00:38:13,721
Was I?

529
00:38:16,931 --> 00:38:17,931
Well, then...

530
00:38:20,901 --> 00:38:22,171
Gosh, how conceited.

531
00:38:23,331 --> 00:38:24,801
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

532
00:38:24,801 --> 00:38:25,801
I heard that.

533
00:38:28,011 --> 00:38:30,541
I meant for you to hear me.

534
00:38:35,181 --> 00:38:39,481
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

535
00:38:39,821 --> 00:38:42,591
I swear I'm going to run her
out of this town.

536
00:38:45,291 --> 00:38:47,221
What? Where did he go?

537
00:38:54,871 --> 00:38:55,871
Hello?

538
00:38:59,571 --> 00:39:01,541
What? Who?

539
00:39:03,511 --> 00:39:06,081
Looks like Bucket's wife
is jealous of you.

540
00:39:06,681 --> 00:39:09,381
Well, it's a classic case
of transference.

541
00:39:09,711 --> 00:39:11,651
A competitive anxiety response,
I'd say.

542
00:39:14,021 --> 00:39:15,021
Hey, so...

543
00:39:15,351 --> 00:39:17,621
Why did you stop by the clinic?
Did you have something to tell me?

544
00:39:19,561 --> 00:39:20,561
Yes.

545
00:39:20,991 --> 00:39:21,991
What is it?

546
00:39:22,731 --> 00:39:24,291
About not wanting to move back here?

547
00:39:25,261 --> 00:39:27,601
The commute is just brutal.

548
00:39:28,101 --> 00:39:31,501
And honestly,
you must've felt it too.

549
00:39:32,141 --> 00:39:34,411
After living apart
for over three years,

550
00:39:34,711 --> 00:39:36,841
it's awkward sleeping together,
you know.

551
00:39:37,411 --> 00:39:39,011
I couldn't even sleep properly
last night.

552
00:39:40,611 --> 00:39:43,351
Okay, I'll talk to my mom about it.

553
00:39:44,381 --> 00:39:45,751
And...

554
00:39:46,951 --> 00:39:50,021
I'm sorry about bringing up divorce.

555
00:39:50,721 --> 00:39:51,961
I was out of line yesterday.

556
00:39:53,461 --> 00:39:57,161
I know what it's like
to feel that loss and helplessness.

557
00:39:59,231 --> 00:40:00,501
I'm sorry, too.

558
00:40:02,831 --> 00:40:05,701
Well, look at that.
The great Han Seong Mi, apologizing.

559
00:40:06,301 --> 00:40:09,271
Please, let's just focus
on our family for a change.

560
00:40:09,741 --> 00:40:11,981
Stop worrying about
everyone else for once, okay?

561
00:40:12,611 --> 00:40:14,481
Hey, but back in the day,

562
00:40:15,181 --> 00:40:17,711
isn't that why you fell for me
in the first place?

563
00:40:18,381 --> 00:40:20,721
Please.
Don't even bring up the past.

564
00:40:21,291 --> 00:40:23,021
I'm the one who dug my own grave.

565
00:40:25,591 --> 00:40:26,791
You dug your own grave?

566
00:40:44,071 --> 00:40:45,311
Beautiful lady.

567
00:40:45,841 --> 00:40:47,081
May I join you?

568
00:40:49,451 --> 00:40:50,451
Oh, my.

569
00:40:52,521 --> 00:40:53,521
My goodness.

570
00:40:55,191 --> 00:40:57,861
It's even better to see you
than I'd imagined.

571
00:41:00,861 --> 00:41:03,161
Gosh, can I...

572
00:41:04,291 --> 00:41:06,631
Can I just give you a hug?

573
00:41:19,281 --> 00:41:20,281
Why isn't she here yet?

574
00:41:21,581 --> 00:41:22,581
Where did she run off to?

575
00:41:25,121 --> 00:41:26,121
(Seoul)

576
00:41:26,851 --> 00:41:27,951
(Wifey)

577
00:41:28,421 --> 00:41:30,751
What? When did she go to Seoul?

578
00:41:32,161 --> 00:41:34,631
What? A hotel?

579
00:41:38,901 --> 00:41:41,701
You've become even more handsome.
So masculine.

580
00:41:42,471 --> 00:41:45,641
Wow, Se Ri.
You haven't changed a bit.

581
00:41:46,001 --> 00:41:47,601
Anyone would believe
you're my girlfriend.

582
00:41:49,211 --> 00:41:51,481
You know I'm deadly serious
about my upkeep.

583
00:41:51,841 --> 00:41:56,111
For us former beauty queens,
our looks are everything.

584
00:42:03,321 --> 00:42:05,661
- How is everyone doing?
- Good.

585
00:42:06,261 --> 00:42:08,891
Speak of the devil.

586
00:42:09,531 --> 00:42:10,991
Is that my dad? Here, let me get it.

587
00:42:15,401 --> 00:42:17,471
- Hello?
- Who is this?

588
00:42:20,001 --> 00:42:21,341
Don't you recognize my voice?

589
00:42:21,671 --> 00:42:23,271
I don't. Who is this, you punk?

590
00:42:23,611 --> 00:42:25,581
What kind of scumbag are you
to be in a hotel with my wife?

591
00:42:26,581 --> 00:42:28,451
What? How did he know
we're at a hotel?

592
00:42:28,911 --> 00:42:30,681
Wait, don't tell me
you're tracking her location.

593
00:42:30,881 --> 00:42:33,281
That's right, you punk.
You're so busted.

594
00:42:33,421 --> 00:42:36,891
Don't you move a muscle.
I'm heading over there now. Got it?

595
00:42:40,661 --> 00:42:41,691
It's me, Dad.

596
00:42:43,761 --> 00:42:45,301
Why, you little...

597
00:42:45,861 --> 00:42:48,171
Hey!
If you were back in town, you punk,

598
00:42:48,731 --> 00:42:50,431
you should have called me first.

599
00:42:51,771 --> 00:42:54,141
Now, you know
who the "other guy" is. Are we good?

600
00:42:54,401 --> 00:42:58,181
Why would you track her?
Seriously, stop. I'm hanging up.

601
00:42:58,241 --> 00:42:59,841
Hey, Hyun Bin! Hey, Yang Hyun Bin!

602
00:43:03,751 --> 00:43:04,751
Thank you.

603
00:43:05,281 --> 00:43:07,021
For putting up
with a man like my father.

604
00:43:08,491 --> 00:43:11,521
Putting up with him?
I'm truly happy.

605
00:43:13,461 --> 00:43:16,091
Doesn't it bother you
that my dad is so suspicious?

606
00:43:18,001 --> 00:43:21,231
I see it as his way
of showing he cares.

607
00:43:22,701 --> 00:43:24,201
Do you really love my father
that much?

608
00:43:27,571 --> 00:43:28,641
I...

609
00:43:29,971 --> 00:43:31,071
I understand him.

610
00:43:31,811 --> 00:43:33,141
He's been through a lot, you know.

611
00:43:34,341 --> 00:43:36,781
His mother left home over an affair,

612
00:43:37,511 --> 00:43:40,021
and his wife cheated on him as well.

613
00:43:44,051 --> 00:43:45,061
I...

614
00:43:46,291 --> 00:43:48,961
I think my grandfather and my dad
were the ones at fault.

615
00:43:49,691 --> 00:43:52,831
I believe that's why they both left.
So...

616
00:43:53,561 --> 00:43:56,301
that's why I can't stand
my grandfather or my dad.

617
00:43:57,531 --> 00:44:00,671
So is that why you left home?
Afraid you'd end up like them?

618
00:44:02,271 --> 00:44:03,371
You're sharp.

619
00:44:07,041 --> 00:44:09,411
So, are you back for good?

620
00:44:09,851 --> 00:44:10,951
No, just for a year.

621
00:44:11,421 --> 00:44:14,181
An old classmate from Argentina
asked me to help her with a project.

622
00:44:15,551 --> 00:44:16,551
"Her?" So, a girl?

623
00:44:17,851 --> 00:44:18,861
Yes.

624
00:44:20,391 --> 00:44:21,831
This should be interesting.

625
00:44:28,001 --> 00:44:29,971
(Taehan)

626
00:44:35,541 --> 00:44:39,581
Remember Manager Kang Min
from our last collaboration?

627
00:44:40,441 --> 00:44:43,581
He's building a new brand's team,
so I put in a good word for you all.

628
00:44:44,051 --> 00:44:47,351
So, everyone, please email him
your resumes and portfolios.

629
00:44:47,951 --> 00:44:49,291
Thanks, boss.

630
00:44:51,291 --> 00:44:54,661
I'm sorry I couldn't stay
with you guys until the end.

631
00:44:55,331 --> 00:44:57,491
Don't say that.
We share the responsibility.

632
00:44:57,891 --> 00:44:59,901
We should have done
one last quality check.

633
00:45:00,731 --> 00:45:04,071
It's awful that you're the only one
whose career is getting tarnished.

634
00:45:06,071 --> 00:45:07,071
Oh, well...

635
00:45:14,281 --> 00:45:15,811
But doesn't it seem really weird?

636
00:45:16,511 --> 00:45:19,251
We ran QC on samples
over three times.

637
00:45:19,251 --> 00:45:20,881
There were no issues at the fitting.

638
00:45:21,421 --> 00:45:24,221
The sourcing team confirmed
the sewing and technical guidelines,

639
00:45:24,591 --> 00:45:26,391
and none of the secondary materials
were defective.

640
00:45:26,661 --> 00:45:29,261
Exactly. You even tried it on
the day before...

641
00:45:29,461 --> 00:45:31,761
and checked the zipper
and all the other parts yourself.

642
00:45:42,771 --> 00:45:43,771
Oh, my.

643
00:45:44,371 --> 00:45:47,141
So, let me get this straight.
You looked like death warmed over,

644
00:45:47,241 --> 00:45:50,751
went completely off-grid,
and made me worry sick,

645
00:45:51,251 --> 00:45:54,081
only to cuddle up and sleep
with a total stranger?

646
00:45:54,221 --> 00:45:57,051
Yes, I was dying
to brag to you about it.

647
00:45:57,251 --> 00:46:02,031
I bet it was nice to be in his arms
after working yourself to death.

648
00:46:02,331 --> 00:46:04,591
See? You get me.

649
00:46:05,501 --> 00:46:06,931
And thanks
for the life-saving chicken feet!

650
00:46:12,601 --> 00:46:15,271
I should be thanking you.
For agreeing to go back to work.

651
00:46:15,611 --> 00:46:16,941
I really thought
you were going to quit.

652
00:46:17,571 --> 00:46:18,581
Tell me about it.

653
00:46:19,981 --> 00:46:23,511
But the kindness of a stranger
really gave me strength.

654
00:46:23,681 --> 00:46:26,581
Goodness.
Are you going to see him again?

655
00:46:26,881 --> 00:46:29,421
What? How could I?
I don't have his number.

656
00:46:30,351 --> 00:46:33,421
I don't even know his first name,
or his last.

657
00:46:33,491 --> 00:46:34,791
I don't know a thing about him.

658
00:46:35,131 --> 00:46:37,061
You should've at least gotten
his number.

659
00:46:38,361 --> 00:46:40,261
The moment was just so perfect
on its own.

660
00:46:41,001 --> 00:46:44,571
I feel like seeing him again
would somehow ruin it, you know?

661
00:46:45,541 --> 00:46:49,311
- If it's meant to be, we'll meet.
- For crying out loud.

662
00:46:53,681 --> 00:46:54,681
Nice.

663
00:46:56,581 --> 00:46:57,851
Man...

664
00:46:59,021 --> 00:47:03,121
Wait, if Hyun Bin is back in Korea,
why is he in a hotel and not home?

665
00:47:03,851 --> 00:47:06,961
He's the eldest son,
yet he does whatever he wants.

666
00:47:08,961 --> 00:47:10,861
Does he really hate
the sight of me that much?

667
00:47:11,361 --> 00:47:15,031
No, Father. He just chose a place
close to the office.

668
00:47:15,731 --> 00:47:19,901
He said he's getting a studio soon.
I told him to come and say hello.

669
00:47:21,541 --> 00:47:23,841
Didn't you tell him to do that?

670
00:47:23,841 --> 00:47:25,081
Because you don't want him
to live with us?

671
00:47:25,441 --> 00:47:29,551
Grandfather, let's be honest.
He went abroad because of her.

672
00:47:30,881 --> 00:47:31,881
Get out.

673
00:47:34,381 --> 00:47:36,691
Goodness. What is going on in there?

674
00:47:37,151 --> 00:47:40,221
- Why can't I hear anything?
- What are you doing? I'm hungry.

675
00:47:40,491 --> 00:47:43,361
Is food all you can think about?
Hyun Bin is back.

676
00:47:43,731 --> 00:47:45,501
If Hyun Bin moves back in,
we'll have to give up our room.

677
00:47:45,931 --> 00:47:48,531
- So, we're getting kicked out?
- Well...

678
00:47:48,831 --> 00:47:49,831
What are you two doing here?

679
00:47:51,841 --> 00:47:54,471
Is Hyun Bin really moving in?

680
00:47:57,941 --> 00:47:59,911
No, he's getting his own place.

681
00:48:02,411 --> 00:48:04,081
Thank goodness.

682
00:48:06,581 --> 00:48:08,721
He said
he'll be in Korea for one year.

683
00:48:09,091 --> 00:48:11,791
I'll use this year to make amends
and make sure he never leaves again.

684
00:48:12,291 --> 00:48:14,931
Don't you worry, Father.
Just leave everything to me.

685
00:48:17,031 --> 00:48:19,831
Do as you see fit, Se Ri.
I trust you.

686
00:48:20,961 --> 00:48:23,431
What are you planning?

687
00:48:24,831 --> 00:48:25,941
As for our Hyun Bin,

688
00:48:27,341 --> 00:48:28,341
I plan on getting him married.

689
00:48:51,361 --> 00:48:53,661
What is wrong with me?

690
00:48:59,901 --> 00:49:02,611
You're fine.

691
00:49:03,341 --> 00:49:07,011
You're fine. You can do this!
I'm so sorry.

692
00:49:08,351 --> 00:49:09,951
- What?
- What?

693
00:49:10,051 --> 00:49:12,281
- What are you doing here?
- I could ask you the same thing.

694
00:49:12,421 --> 00:49:13,981
Wait, are you here to see me?

695
00:49:14,251 --> 00:49:16,521
- Of course not.
- Then why?

696
00:49:17,151 --> 00:49:19,561
- It must be a coincidence.
- There's no way.

697
00:49:20,161 --> 00:49:21,461
If not a coincidence, then what?

698
00:49:21,991 --> 00:49:25,601
Don't tell me you got the wrong idea
about me from the other night.

699
00:49:26,101 --> 00:49:27,101
What?

700
00:49:27,101 --> 00:49:31,471
Is this all because we fell asleep
holding each other?

701
00:49:31,741 --> 00:49:33,871
What? We slept in each other's arms?

702
00:49:34,241 --> 00:49:37,611
No. Nothing like that ever happened.

703
00:49:38,241 --> 00:49:42,851
Then this must be a coincidence.
And this is where it ends.

704
00:49:42,851 --> 00:49:45,021
Got it? Don't follow me.

705
00:50:04,471 --> 00:50:05,501
What is with this guy?

706
00:50:06,771 --> 00:50:07,801
Security! Over here!

707
00:50:08,811 --> 00:50:10,071
Please stop that man!

708
00:50:11,641 --> 00:50:12,641
Seriously?

709
00:50:13,481 --> 00:50:14,481
Unbelievable.

710
00:50:15,651 --> 00:50:17,881
Excuse me, Ms. Gong Ju Ah,
let me explain.

711
00:50:18,311 --> 00:50:21,951
How do you know my name?
You saw that video of me!

712
00:50:22,421 --> 00:50:24,921
- He's a stalker! A stalker!
- Come on.

713
00:50:25,121 --> 00:50:28,361
- Seriously.
- No! I'm not a stalker.

714
00:50:28,491 --> 00:50:31,561
- Sir, please calm down and listen.
- What's going on?

715
00:50:31,561 --> 00:50:32,661
I'm not a stalker.

716
00:50:35,771 --> 00:50:37,901
What's wrong? Who is this guy?

717
00:50:38,701 --> 00:50:43,471
- Let's just go. Come on. Seriously.
- Excuse me! Can we just talk?

718
00:50:43,911 --> 00:50:46,611
I'm really not a stalker. Look.

719
00:50:46,611 --> 00:50:47,841
I start working here today...

720
00:50:47,841 --> 00:50:48,911
Pacu Nacho?

721
00:50:53,381 --> 00:50:56,691
Hye Su. Help me out here.

722
00:50:58,021 --> 00:50:59,821
Let him go. He's an employee.

723
00:51:04,991 --> 00:51:07,331
You finally made it, Pacu Nacho.

724
00:51:08,431 --> 00:51:10,671
I know, right? How long has it been?

725
00:51:21,851 --> 00:51:23,651
That's the guy you slept with?

726
00:51:27,521 --> 00:51:28,521
Sorry.

727
00:51:29,751 --> 00:51:30,821
Hold on.

728
00:51:31,451 --> 00:51:33,691
Didn't you say you didn't have
his number or anything?

729
00:51:34,491 --> 00:51:36,161
Did you happen to mention
where you work or something?

730
00:51:36,731 --> 00:51:38,391
I think he saw
the home shopping video.

731
00:51:40,861 --> 00:51:43,601
This is a big deal.

732
00:51:46,971 --> 00:51:49,211
(Taehan Home Shopping Special)

733
00:51:49,271 --> 00:51:52,111
Was this really a mistake?

734
00:51:52,641 --> 00:51:54,211
Don't you think
we should look into this?

735
00:51:54,681 --> 00:51:55,681
You handle it.

736
00:51:56,411 --> 00:51:58,411
Let's sort out
your work schedule first.

737
00:51:58,951 --> 00:52:00,451
We're in a really bad spot
right now.

738
00:52:00,881 --> 00:52:03,491
We're losing our competitive edge
to imported brands.

739
00:52:03,751 --> 00:52:04,891
That's why I'm here.

740
00:52:05,361 --> 00:52:07,721
With an instinct for branding
that anticipates trends...

741
00:52:08,161 --> 00:52:11,261
and a reputation
for one-of-a-kind marketing,

742
00:52:11,861 --> 00:52:13,061
Pacu Nacho Yang.

743
00:52:13,461 --> 00:52:14,801
I'm so grateful.

744
00:52:15,371 --> 00:52:17,031
Thanks for answering my S.O.S.
on such short notice.

745
00:52:17,331 --> 00:52:19,841
When I was broke back in Argentina,

746
00:52:19,901 --> 00:52:22,711
you always bought me food
and helped me get through school.

747
00:52:22,971 --> 00:52:25,711
- Of course, I have to repay you.
- I guess the meals really paid off.

748
00:52:26,281 --> 00:52:28,411
- You start tomorrow?
- Sure. Why not?

749
00:52:29,281 --> 00:52:30,351
Wait.

750
00:52:31,151 --> 00:52:34,751
As head of the fashion division,
do I have hiring and firing power?

751
00:52:35,791 --> 00:52:36,791
Unbelievable.

752
00:52:41,831 --> 00:52:44,161
I went back to the lobby,
but that jerk was gone.

753
00:52:44,661 --> 00:52:45,661
My gosh.

754
00:52:46,261 --> 00:52:47,861
Isn't it weird, though?

755
00:52:48,231 --> 00:52:51,771
Once a guy falls for me,
he'll stop at nothing.

756
00:52:51,871 --> 00:52:55,211
Hey.
Enough with the unconfirmed stories.

757
00:52:55,711 --> 00:52:57,371
And get going.
The vice president's asking for you.

758
00:52:58,311 --> 00:52:59,541
The vice president?

759
00:53:01,111 --> 00:53:02,511
After an internal review,

760
00:53:03,081 --> 00:53:05,251
regarding the recent
home shopping broadcast incident,

761
00:53:05,851 --> 00:53:09,891
we've decided to ask
for your resignation, Ms. Gong.

762
00:53:11,321 --> 00:53:15,731
I thought the penalty for losing
was a demotion.

763
00:53:15,991 --> 00:53:20,331
That only applies if you fall behind
in a performance review.

764
00:53:21,101 --> 00:53:24,571
This incident not only damaged
our brand's public image,

765
00:53:24,631 --> 00:53:27,371
but it also undermined
the trust in our quality control.

766
00:53:27,871 --> 00:53:31,641
I'm sorry.
I have no excuse for that.

767
00:53:32,641 --> 00:53:33,641
But...

768
00:53:34,081 --> 00:53:37,311
even if I have to quit,
please let me investigate this.

769
00:53:38,511 --> 00:53:39,521
An investigation?

770
00:53:39,851 --> 00:53:43,751
I believe that someone intentionally
interfered with this.

771
00:53:44,351 --> 00:53:46,561
I want to be the one
to uncover the truth.

772
00:53:47,161 --> 00:53:48,561
I can't just leave like this.

773
00:53:50,891 --> 00:53:52,201
Someone once told me...

774
00:53:53,201 --> 00:53:54,201
that I...

775
00:53:55,031 --> 00:53:56,731
am someone who creates happiness.

776
00:53:58,801 --> 00:54:03,241
I want people to feel happy
when they wear the clothes I design.

777
00:54:04,211 --> 00:54:06,841
I don't want
to leave in disgrace like this.

778
00:54:07,411 --> 00:54:08,411
Please.

779
00:54:16,751 --> 00:54:19,061
You'll work under
the new executive director.

780
00:54:22,061 --> 00:54:23,831
Yes. Of course.

781
00:54:24,061 --> 00:54:28,501
But isn't he a foreigner?
I'm not sure if I can...

782
00:54:28,561 --> 00:54:31,631
- communicate with him...
- Make an effort.

783
00:54:32,701 --> 00:54:35,201
I'm waiving disciplinary action,
so it's the least you can do.

784
00:54:35,941 --> 00:54:39,841
Yes, I'll do my best.
Thank you, Vice President.

785
00:54:41,381 --> 00:54:42,381
Well, then...

786
00:54:44,611 --> 00:54:45,751
But, Vice President...

787
00:54:47,551 --> 00:54:50,551
Be careful.
There's a lunatic in the lobby.

788
00:54:51,851 --> 00:54:52,861
What?

789
00:54:53,221 --> 00:54:54,291
You see,

790
00:54:54,521 --> 00:54:57,591
I happened to run into him
a couple of days ago.

791
00:54:57,791 --> 00:55:00,231
But I never thought he'd follow me
all the way to the office.

792
00:55:00,901 --> 00:55:02,931
He must be some unhinged stalker.

793
00:55:04,531 --> 00:55:07,101
I just thought you should be aware.

794
00:55:08,341 --> 00:55:09,341
I'll be on my way.

795
00:55:12,911 --> 00:55:14,911
(Taehan Group)

796
00:55:26,691 --> 00:55:28,161
What's going on, Pacu Nacho?

797
00:55:29,161 --> 00:55:30,461
(Taehan Group)

798
00:55:30,531 --> 00:55:32,201
What was that about with Gong Ju Ah?

799
00:55:35,731 --> 00:55:37,931
I'm kind of excited.

800
00:55:38,471 --> 00:55:39,741
About life at this company.

801
00:55:43,071 --> 00:55:45,441
(President of the Association
of Korean Medicine)

802
00:55:45,511 --> 00:55:48,951
Our Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic
has been completely renovated!

803
00:55:49,011 --> 00:55:51,551
Please take one. Both our treatments
and our service...

804
00:55:51,611 --> 00:55:54,981
are on a whole new level of class.
Please come visit!

805
00:55:55,051 --> 00:55:58,761
Right! Visit for a free consultation
and enjoy a warm welcome tea.

806
00:55:58,821 --> 00:56:00,021
Here, take one.

807
00:56:00,461 --> 00:56:04,491
Stop by. We'll provide service
that's in a class of its own.

808
00:56:04,761 --> 00:56:05,801
Excuse me, sir.

809
00:56:08,971 --> 00:56:11,301
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

810
00:56:11,301 --> 00:56:13,071
Where's Eun Bin?
Why isn't she out here helping?

811
00:56:13,571 --> 00:56:15,301
She's inside, filming a vlog.

812
00:56:16,111 --> 00:56:17,271
She's so annoying.

813
00:56:17,611 --> 00:56:19,641
How will we get any customers
like this?

814
00:56:20,111 --> 00:56:23,811
- Just wait. I've planned it all.
- Planned what?

815
00:56:27,351 --> 00:56:28,751
Here she comes.

816
00:56:31,951 --> 00:56:32,991
What's this?

817
00:56:34,091 --> 00:56:38,861
Hey, everyone!
It's Yanggaeng, from Sunny TV.

818
00:56:39,131 --> 00:56:42,601
You know that place that's a big hit
with the moms in Onjeong right now?

819
00:56:42,871 --> 00:56:44,331
The holy grail of Korean medicine,

820
00:56:44,331 --> 00:56:46,971
Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic,
has been renovated,

821
00:56:47,041 --> 00:56:48,771
so I had to come
to check it out myself.

822
00:56:48,841 --> 00:56:50,141
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

823
00:56:50,211 --> 00:56:51,971
How luxurious!

824
00:56:52,641 --> 00:56:54,441
It's like a hotel lounge, isn't it?

825
00:56:56,211 --> 00:57:00,151
This is the star of our clinic,

826
00:57:00,281 --> 00:57:02,421
Director Yang Seon Chul.

827
00:57:02,791 --> 00:57:06,921
He's a specialist in chronic illness
and can diagnose you by your pulse.

828
00:57:07,891 --> 00:57:09,361
Say a few words for us, Director.

829
00:57:10,031 --> 00:57:11,191
Get out.

830
00:57:16,571 --> 00:57:18,671
Yes! Looks like a chicken dinner
for me tonight.

831
00:57:19,241 --> 00:57:22,111
- Why won't you die, stupid thing?
- Ta-da!

832
00:57:23,271 --> 00:57:25,441
Next, our specialist for skin...

833
00:57:25,441 --> 00:57:27,611
and weight management
for VIP clients...

834
00:57:27,681 --> 00:57:32,051
is Director Yang Dong Ik. Director,
what's your signature treatment?

835
00:57:32,521 --> 00:57:35,851
It brightens skin, clears blemishes,
and reduces wrinkles all at once.

836
00:57:35,921 --> 00:57:37,821
It's our Multi-Skin
Youth-Restoring Acupuncture.

837
00:57:39,361 --> 00:57:42,731
See my firm, radiant skin?
The secret to my complexion is...

838
00:57:42,791 --> 00:57:47,701
his signature treatment!
This is Yanggaeng, signing off.

839
00:57:50,771 --> 00:57:54,371
Gosh, that was exhausting.
Dad, you'd better pay me for this.

840
00:57:54,441 --> 00:57:55,771
Ten dollars per like.

841
00:57:56,371 --> 00:58:00,081
- Hey, are there any customers?
- No. They're across the street.

842
00:58:00,411 --> 00:58:02,651
- Why?
- I don't know. A flea market maybe?

843
00:58:02,651 --> 00:58:03,711
It's packed.

844
00:58:04,951 --> 00:58:06,581
Why today, of all days?

845
00:58:08,181 --> 00:58:09,291
Unbelievable.

846
00:58:11,321 --> 00:58:14,821
Everyone, Sang Gu's mother is
closing her long-running store,

847
00:58:14,991 --> 00:58:19,101
so everything's on a huge discount.
Come and take a look for yourself.

848
00:58:20,801 --> 00:58:22,971
This way, my patients can buy things
on their way in and out.

849
00:58:23,401 --> 00:58:25,331
So just leave everything here
until it's all sold out.

850
00:58:25,901 --> 00:58:29,911
Thank you so much. I was about
to sell it all for next to nothing.

851
00:58:30,641 --> 00:58:32,381
After running the shop
for over 30 years,

852
00:58:33,041 --> 00:58:34,211
it must be so hard to let it go.

853
00:58:34,841 --> 00:58:37,451
They suddenly hiked the rent
by 500 dollars.

854
00:58:38,611 --> 00:58:39,821
What choice did I have?

855
00:58:40,051 --> 00:58:43,321
I don't know what's with everyone,
suddenly raising all the rents.

856
00:58:43,551 --> 00:58:45,921
Tell me about it.
The bedding store is for sale, too.

857
00:58:45,991 --> 00:58:48,761
- The head merchant is selling up.
- Really?

858
00:58:50,391 --> 00:58:52,761
What's all that noise?

859
00:58:53,101 --> 00:58:55,631
It's the grand reopening
for that other clinic today.

860
00:58:55,731 --> 00:58:59,141
Seriously, talk about not being able
to read the room.

861
00:58:59,201 --> 00:59:00,501
- Hey, come on.
- Take it easy.

862
00:59:00,571 --> 00:59:02,711
- Just stay out of it.
- Let it go.

863
00:59:03,341 --> 00:59:04,471
I'll handle it.

864
00:59:04,541 --> 00:59:06,581
(Nurse Oh Jin Ah)

865
00:59:06,641 --> 00:59:09,181
- Thank you.
- Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic!

866
00:59:09,181 --> 00:59:10,781
Yes. We recently renovated.

867
00:59:10,911 --> 00:59:13,721
Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic
has been newly renovated! Here.

868
00:59:14,051 --> 00:59:15,081
- Right over here.
- Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic.

869
00:59:15,151 --> 00:59:16,591
- Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic.
- Thank you.

870
00:59:16,851 --> 00:59:18,691
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

871
00:59:18,751 --> 00:59:19,761
Welcome
to Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic.

872
00:59:20,521 --> 00:59:23,591
- Thank you. Please take one.
- Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic!

873
00:59:23,891 --> 00:59:26,601
We've newly renovated.
Please take one.

874
00:59:30,431 --> 00:59:33,501
Excuse me.
We received a noise complaint,

875
00:59:33,571 --> 00:59:34,771
so we were dispatched to the scene.

876
00:59:36,171 --> 00:59:37,571
A noise complaint?

877
00:59:37,971 --> 00:59:40,281
This isn't a residential area.
It's a market.

878
00:59:40,341 --> 00:59:42,951
Even in a market, we must enforce
the rules if there is a complaint.

879
00:59:43,351 --> 00:59:47,081
The daytime limit is 70 decibels.
You need to stay below that.

880
00:59:48,181 --> 00:59:49,521
See? You're over the limit.

881
00:59:50,821 --> 00:59:52,491
Who on earth would report
something like this?

882
00:59:53,391 --> 00:59:56,831
I can't disclose who reported this.
Their identity is protected.

883
00:59:57,531 --> 00:59:59,231
I don't need you to tell me.
I know exactly who it was.

884
01:00:00,231 --> 01:00:01,601
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

885
01:00:03,071 --> 01:00:05,941
Gosh, it's cold.

886
01:00:06,271 --> 01:00:07,271
All right.

887
01:00:07,801 --> 01:00:10,411
We'll turn the music off.
Please turn it off.

888
01:00:11,141 --> 01:00:13,081
Thank you for your cooperation.
I'll be on my way.

889
01:00:13,141 --> 01:00:14,811
Why are you turning off the music?
Who gave you the right?

890
01:00:15,581 --> 01:00:16,711
Hurry up and turn it back on.

891
01:00:17,611 --> 01:00:21,151
Officer, that clinic over there
is openly selling merchandise.

892
01:00:21,651 --> 01:00:24,351
If they're making untaxed profit,
isn't that tax evasion?

893
01:00:25,121 --> 01:00:28,791
For tax evasion, call the tax office
at 126. That's not my jurisdiction.

894
01:00:29,661 --> 01:00:33,061
Let it go, Director.
We knew this was going to happen.

895
01:00:33,531 --> 01:00:36,071
This will all be over in a few days,
so let's just be patient, okay?

896
01:00:36,871 --> 01:00:38,101
You might as well
just sell your clinic.

897
01:00:40,001 --> 01:00:42,611
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic,
Pharmacy)

898
01:00:43,371 --> 01:00:46,041
- Mom, let's call it a day.
- Just a second. I'm on the phone.

899
01:00:48,381 --> 01:00:49,481
Yes.

900
01:00:49,981 --> 01:00:52,781
Let me talk it over
with my kids first.

901
01:00:53,781 --> 01:00:54,781
Okay.

902
01:00:55,921 --> 01:00:57,521
What is it? What's going on?

903
01:00:58,691 --> 01:01:01,891
He's asking us for more rent, too.

904
01:01:04,431 --> 01:01:05,561
Unbelievable.

905
01:01:06,561 --> 01:01:10,701
A 20 percent increase?
You know we can't afford that.

906
01:01:10,971 --> 01:01:12,501
I'm very sorry, ma'am.

907
01:01:12,901 --> 01:01:15,501
Sir, would you care to explain?

908
01:01:15,811 --> 01:01:17,741
What in the world is going on here?

909
01:01:18,971 --> 01:01:20,081
The thing is...

910
01:01:20,681 --> 01:01:23,211
The landlords all had
a meeting recently.

911
01:01:26,821 --> 01:01:31,121
So, to make the market look better,
you want to get rid of old shops...

912
01:01:31,191 --> 01:01:33,421
and replace them all
with franchises?

913
01:01:34,561 --> 01:01:35,961
I'm not saying we get rid of them,

914
01:01:36,131 --> 01:01:41,001
- but to switch to a stable model.
- But listen.

915
01:01:41,301 --> 01:01:42,971
Hasn't business been good lately?

916
01:01:43,431 --> 01:01:46,071
The new apartment complex
has brought in more people,

917
01:01:46,401 --> 01:01:47,941
and none of the tenants
are behind on rent.

918
01:01:48,971 --> 01:01:50,911
That's just a flash in the pan,
all right?

919
01:01:51,271 --> 01:01:54,311
Young people these days
don't come to the market to shop.

920
01:01:54,581 --> 01:01:57,811
They buy everything on their phones.
Isn't that right?

921
01:01:59,011 --> 01:02:02,821
You're familiar with Gopyeong Market
in Sodang City, right?

922
01:02:03,491 --> 01:02:07,991
They partnered with Soban Company
and franchised the entire market,

923
01:02:08,321 --> 01:02:09,391
and their sales...

924
01:02:10,191 --> 01:02:11,761
increased tenfold.

925
01:02:12,501 --> 01:02:17,031
Right, I saw that on the news.
They sell 10,000 donuts a day,

926
01:02:17,231 --> 01:02:19,541
and they're making 5,000 dollars
a day.

927
01:02:19,841 --> 01:02:22,611
But the shop owners here...

928
01:02:22,871 --> 01:02:26,541
have been in the same spot
for 20 or 30 years.

929
01:02:28,511 --> 01:02:30,281
Do you really think
they'll cooperate?

930
01:02:31,551 --> 01:02:33,021
If they won't leave,

931
01:02:33,981 --> 01:02:37,821
- we make them leave.
- Come on. You think it's that easy?

932
01:02:38,221 --> 01:02:40,661
Well, raise the rent.

933
01:02:41,491 --> 01:02:44,361
If they can't afford it,
they'll have to leave.

934
01:02:46,701 --> 01:02:50,171
I'm sure I can count on all of you.
Now, let's have a drink.

935
01:02:51,801 --> 01:02:52,971
I'm counting on your support.

936
01:02:54,941 --> 01:02:56,841
That jerk.

937
01:02:57,971 --> 01:02:59,881
I am so sorry about this.

938
01:03:10,151 --> 01:03:14,361
- You scared me.
- Hey, what the heck are you doing?

939
01:03:14,921 --> 01:03:16,861
What are you talking about?
This is completely out of the blue.

940
01:03:17,331 --> 01:03:20,031
- What do you mean? What did I do?
- Are you playing dumb?

941
01:03:20,601 --> 01:03:24,001
You gathered all the landlords
with leases about to expire...

942
01:03:24,201 --> 01:03:26,141
and got them to raise
the rent prices, didn't you?

943
01:03:26,441 --> 01:03:29,411
You know that's a violation
of the Fair Trade Act.

944
01:03:29,471 --> 01:03:31,971
Hey, the rent going up doesn't
automatically make it illegal.

945
01:03:33,541 --> 01:03:36,781
As if bleeding the elderly dry
with overtreatment wasn't enough,

946
01:03:36,851 --> 01:03:40,981
you'd kick them out
and threaten their livelihoods?

947
01:03:41,051 --> 01:03:42,651
Just be honest, you jerk.

948
01:03:42,951 --> 01:03:44,521
You don't care about the market,
do you?

949
01:03:44,851 --> 01:03:47,821
You're scared your clinic
will go under if they all leave.

950
01:03:47,891 --> 01:03:49,891
But don't you worry.

951
01:03:50,461 --> 01:03:52,191
Because you'll be leaving
soon enough anyway.

952
01:03:52,701 --> 01:03:54,301
You got that call, didn't you?

953
01:03:54,801 --> 01:03:55,801
Hey, you...

954
01:03:56,431 --> 01:04:00,001
Don't tell me the real reason
for this is to kick out my clinic.

955
01:04:00,201 --> 01:04:01,201
Hey.

956
01:04:02,071 --> 01:04:04,011
I'm genuinely curious
about something.

957
01:04:04,511 --> 01:04:06,041
Do you think
the world revolves around you?

958
01:04:07,341 --> 01:04:10,911
As your wife, Seong Mi, always says,
being delusional is a sickness.

959
01:04:11,381 --> 01:04:14,481
Psychoanalytically speaking,
you have an overinflated ego.

960
01:04:14,681 --> 01:04:17,291
You jerk.
Do you really have to go this far?

961
01:04:17,421 --> 01:04:20,661
Hey, you'd better start looking
for a new place for your clinic.

962
01:04:20,991 --> 01:04:23,031
And maybe start making
some real money.

963
01:04:23,531 --> 01:04:27,331
You're not getting any younger.
How long will you leech off her?

964
01:04:28,361 --> 01:04:29,371
You son of a...

965
01:04:35,501 --> 01:04:39,311
Gosh, what's with that family?
I mean, they're loaded.

966
01:04:39,381 --> 01:04:42,341
If they hate seeing us so much,
they should be the ones to move.

967
01:04:42,781 --> 01:04:45,151
I heard the grandfather won't leave.
It's his hometown.

968
01:04:45,411 --> 01:04:48,551
Sure, Yang Dong Ik thinks
it was our fault his mom left.

969
01:04:48,581 --> 01:04:51,391
So of course, he resents us.
But hey, because of his family,

970
01:04:51,451 --> 01:04:52,791
I grew up without a father,
so what's the big deal?

971
01:04:53,491 --> 01:04:58,131
That's true. His son's grandma
and mom had affairs,

972
01:04:58,191 --> 01:05:00,661
so he was always getting teased
and beat up for it.

973
01:05:01,831 --> 01:05:05,571
- I stood up for him a few times.
- Yes, that's right.

974
01:05:06,471 --> 01:05:09,741
- What was that guy's name again?
- Yang Hyun Bin?

975
01:05:10,511 --> 01:05:12,341
Hey! Yang Hyun Bin.

976
01:05:12,781 --> 01:05:15,541
Is that the kid who kept visiting
before he left to study abroad?

977
01:05:16,681 --> 01:05:17,981
- That's him.
- My gosh.

978
01:05:17,981 --> 01:05:19,681
I'm pretty sure
he had a huge crush on her.

979
01:05:21,151 --> 01:05:24,921
Yes, I guess he did. Anyway,
I wonder what he's up to now.

980
01:05:25,091 --> 01:05:26,521
I wonder if he even remembers me.

981
01:05:29,591 --> 01:05:32,601
(Taehan)

982
01:05:32,701 --> 01:05:35,131
(Taehan Group)

983
01:05:37,101 --> 01:05:38,131
Ju Ah.

984
01:05:39,231 --> 01:05:41,441
What's the name of the new director
you'll be working for?

985
01:05:42,241 --> 01:05:45,411
Pacundo Ignacio de la Cruz Yang.

986
01:05:45,981 --> 01:05:47,811
With Yang in the name,
I'm guessing it's a woman.

987
01:05:50,411 --> 01:05:54,181
- Isn't Yang the last name?
- Is that it?

988
01:05:55,551 --> 01:05:57,521
Then I guess he's not a foreigner.

989
01:05:57,851 --> 01:05:58,921
Maybe he's a Korean
who grew up abroad?

990
01:06:11,331 --> 01:06:15,201
It's been a while since our division
was all gathered in one place.

991
01:06:15,571 --> 01:06:17,671
You've all heard the news, right?

992
01:06:23,011 --> 01:06:27,251
Meet our new General Director,
who'll be joining us as of today.

993
01:06:28,121 --> 01:06:30,591
Please come in! Pacu Nacho!

994
01:06:36,961 --> 01:06:40,201
What? Who does he think he is,
a movie star? So dramatic.

995
01:07:00,651 --> 01:07:01,651
Hello, everyone.

996
01:07:02,721 --> 01:07:04,121
A pleasure to meet you all.

997
01:07:06,061 --> 01:07:09,291
Nice to meet you all.
Yes, it's great to meet you.

998
01:07:09,491 --> 01:07:10,591
Nice to meet you.

999
01:07:13,701 --> 01:07:14,931
(Dr. Hub)

1000
01:07:15,001 --> 01:07:17,131
(Clinic Space for Sale or Lease)

1001
01:07:17,201 --> 01:07:18,201
(Clinic Space for Sale or Lease)

1002
01:07:23,911 --> 01:07:25,571
Jeong Han!

1003
01:07:26,141 --> 01:07:28,341
Hey! You are not going
to believe this.

1004
01:07:28,411 --> 01:07:30,851
Bucket is running for president
of the Merchants' Association.

1005
01:07:32,211 --> 01:07:34,551
Him? President?
That's completely out of left field.

1006
01:07:34,651 --> 01:07:36,521
I overheard it at the snack bar...

1007
01:07:36,651 --> 01:07:41,061
- that Bucket's running for council.
- What?

1008
01:07:41,121 --> 01:07:45,891
He's scheming to become president
and make the market his voter base!

1009
01:07:46,761 --> 01:07:48,561
That jerk...

1010
01:07:51,171 --> 01:07:54,071
All right,
if there are no other candidates,

1011
01:07:55,071 --> 01:07:58,811
Dr. Yang Dong Ik will be considered
the sole nominee,

1012
01:07:59,111 --> 01:08:00,311
and without an election,

1013
01:08:01,081 --> 01:08:03,211
he will be declared the winner.

1014
01:08:03,551 --> 01:08:07,021
Does anyone else wish
to register as a candidate?

1015
01:08:09,491 --> 01:08:11,151
- All right, then.
- I do.

1016
01:08:15,021 --> 01:08:16,431
- What?
- What's this all of a sudden?

1017
01:08:21,301 --> 01:08:23,401
I'm running for president
of the Merchants' Association.

1018
01:08:24,131 --> 01:08:26,871
Hey, are you nuts?
Seong Mi will flip if she finds out.

1019
01:08:27,201 --> 01:08:28,671
Keep it down, man.

1020
01:08:29,471 --> 01:08:31,871
Well, Dr. Gong.

1021
01:08:32,881 --> 01:08:34,211
So, you're throwing your hat
in the ring?

1022
01:08:36,411 --> 01:08:39,651
How do you possibly think
you can handle it?

1023
01:08:41,981 --> 01:08:44,251
What's wrong? Getting cold feet?

1024
01:08:45,121 --> 01:08:47,391
Then you should just fold.

1025
01:08:54,431 --> 01:08:57,031
(Special thanks to Go Myung Hwan
and Jo Seung Je)

1026
01:09:18,221 --> 01:09:20,791
(Recipe For Love)

1027
01:09:20,891 --> 01:09:22,591
It's me, the creepy stalker.

1028
01:09:22,691 --> 01:09:25,061
I believe this is the first time
we've met, sir.

1029
01:09:26,061 --> 01:09:28,731
- Does Gong Ju Ah know it's you?
- Again.

1030
01:09:29,101 --> 01:09:30,601
What are you going to do
when Seong Mi finds out?

1031
01:09:30,771 --> 01:09:32,571
You think I can't convince her?

1032
01:09:32,571 --> 01:09:33,941
Just this once, okay?

1033
01:09:34,001 --> 01:09:35,941
When have you ever kept your word?

1034
01:09:36,001 --> 01:09:37,711
The election is next week.
You really think you can win?

1035
01:09:37,771 --> 01:09:40,081
I'm the most popular guy
in all of Onjeong Market.

1036
01:09:40,141 --> 01:09:42,141
Everyone hates my brother.

1037
01:09:42,211 --> 01:09:44,451
Politics isn't about
what voters want.

1038
01:09:44,451 --> 01:09:46,151
It's about shaping it.

1039
01:09:47,021 --> 01:09:50,691
My dad or your dad?
That is the question.

1040
01:09:50,751 --> 01:09:52,251
I'm rooting for your dad.

1041
01:09:52,321 --> 01:09:55,221
There's no point in fighting
a losing battle, is there?

1042
01:09:56,139 --> 01:09:58,139
Dramaday.me
